.B
pushAttrib(Mask) -> ok
.br
.RS
.LP
Types:

.RS 3
Mask = integer()
.br
.RE
.RE
.RS
.LP
Push and pop the server attribute stack
.LP
\fIgl:pushAttrib\fR\& takes one argument, a mask that indicates which groups of state variables to save on the attribute stack\&. Symbolic constants are used to set bits in the mask\&. \fIMask\fR\& is typically constructed by specifying the bitwise-or of several of these constants together\&. The special mask \fI?GL_ALL_ATTRIB_BITS\fR\& can be used to save all stackable states\&.
.LP
See external documentation\&.
.RE
.LP
.B
popAttrib() -> ok
.br
.RS
.LP
See \fBpushAttrib/1\fR\&
.RE
.LP
